{"word":"ἀνήκοος","slug":"ἀνήκοος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνήκοος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀκοή'><el>ἀκοή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>without hearing</i>, of the dead, <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>not hearing</i> a thing, <i>never having heard</i> it, <i>ignorant</i> of it, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>σκαιὸς καὶ ἀν.</el> <i>ignorant</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}